{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T09:57:32.139Z","taskId":"KB-001","text":"task_create","type":"tool","detail":"## Goal\nBuild a persistent sticky-bottom audio player bar that continues playing across Astro page navigations using View Transitions.\n\n## Tech Details from Research\n- **Waveform:** wavesurfer.js v7 for waveform visualization\n- **Audio engine:** howler.js as cross-browser audio engine (format fallback MP3/OGG, Web Audio API)\n- **Playlist support:** play/pause, next/prev, progress bar, volume, track title + artist display\n- **Persistence:** Astro island (client-side JS component) that persists via View Transitions `transition:persist`\n- **Audio hosting:** Files served from Cloudflare R2 (URLs configured via env variable `R2_PUBLIC_URL`)\n\n## Deliverables\n- `src/components/AudioPlayer/` directory containing:\n  - Player component (Astro island with client-side JS)\n  - Playlist store (track list, current track, playback state)\n  - Waveform renderer (wavesurfer.js integration)\n  - Howler wrapper (audio engine abstraction)\n- CSS for sticky bottom bar styling\n- Player-reactive state that survives page transitions\n- `.env.example` entry for `R2_PUBLIC_URL`\n\n## Dependencies\nKB-002 (project scaffolding must exist)\n\n## Size\nL","agent":"executor"}
