{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T09:58:25.457Z","taskId":"KB-001","text":"task_create","type":"tool","detail":"## Goal\nSet up deployment pipeline: Cloudflare Pages for the Astro site, Cloudflare R2 bucket for audio files, and CI/CD configuration.\n\n## Tech Details from Research\n- **Astro adapter:** `@astrojs/cloudflare` for server-side rendering support\n- **Config:** `wrangler.toml` for Cloudflare Pages configuration\n- **Audio hosting:** R2 bucket (free tier: 10 GB storage, free egress) — enough for ~100-200 MP3s\n- **Build:** `npm run build`, output to `dist/`\n- **Environment variables:** R2 public URL for audio file references\n- **DNS:** Custom domain setup (documented, not automated)\n\n## Deliverables\n- `wrangler.toml` — Cloudflare Pages configuration\n- Updated `astro.config.mjs` with Cloudflare adapter\n- `docs/deployment.md` — step-by-step setup guide covering:\n  - R2 bucket creation and public access configuration\n  - Pages project linking and build settings\n  - DNS configuration (CNAME to Pages)\n  - Environment variables setup\n- `.env.example` updated with deployment-related vars\n\n## Dependencies\nKB-002 (scaffolding), KB-003 (audio player — needs R2 URL config), KB-006 (SEO — needs production URL for canonical tags)\n\n## Size\nM","agent":"executor"}
